Definition: an ancient musical horn made from the horn of a ram
Example: used in ancient times by the Israelites to sound a warning or a summons; used in synagogues today on solemn occasions
Synonyms: shophar, horn, an, ancient, musical, made, from, the, of, a, ram, used, in, times, by, Israelites, to, sound, warning, or, summons, synagogues, today, on, solemn, occasions
Category: noun.artifact
